qas.question: The abbey was recognised as what until 1556?

answers.text: a second cathedral of the Diocese of London

qas.question: Who is the abbey dedicated to?

plausible_answers.text: a second cathedral of the Diocese of London

qas.question: The abbey was recognised as what after 1556?

plausible_answers.text: a second cathedral of the Diocese of London

qas.question: The abbey was recognised as what until 1565?
Who isn't the abbey dedicated to?

context: Westminster diocese was dissolved in <a0_0><b3_0><b4_0>1550<b4_0/><b3_0/><a0_0/>, but the abbey was recognised (in 1552, retroactively to 1550) as <a1_0><b5_0><b6_0>a second cathedral of the Diocese of London<b6_0/><b5_0/><a1_0/> until 1556. The already-old expression "robbing Peter to pay Paul" may have been given a new lease of life when money meant for the abbey, which is dedicated to <a2_0><b7_0>Saint Peter<b7_0/><a2_0/>, was diverted to the treasury of St Paul's Cathedral.
